{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1ecafaa-7baa-49d6-93f4-7afff87fff0c","content":"You're on .NET 10. Here's the concrete plan:\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-step: MAUI Android on headless Linux\n\n### 1. Install the MAUI Android workload & discover required versions\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload install maui-android\n```\n\nAfter install, **find the exact Android dependencies it expects**:\n\n```bash\n# Shows the Android API level and build-tools version the workload targets\ndotnet workload list\ncat /usr/share/dotnet/packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.Linux/*/AutoImport.props 2>/dev/null\n# Or inspect the resolved manifest:\nls /usr/share/dotnet/sdk-manifests/\n```\n\nThe workload pins specific versions (e.g., API 35, build-tools 35.0.0). Read them before proceeding.\n\n### 2. Install JDK 17\n\nMAUI/.NET Android requires **JDK 17** (not 21):\n\n```bash\nsudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n```\n\n### 3. Install Android SDK (command-line tools only)\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_SDK_ROOT=\"$HOME/android-sdk\"\nmkdir -p \"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools\"\n\n# Download latest command-line tools\ncurl -fsSL https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-11076708_latest.zip \\\n  -o /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip\nunzip -q /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip -d \"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools\"\nmv \"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools/cmdline-tools\" \"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools/latest\"\n```\n\n### 4. Accept licenses & install the exact SDK components\n\nUse the versions you discovered in step 1:\n\n```bash\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$PATH\"\n\nyes | sdkmanager --licenses\n\n# Replace API/build-tools versions with what the workload requires\nsdkmanager \\\n  \"platform-tools\" \\\n  \"platforms;android-35\" \\\n  \"build-tools;35.0.0\"\n```\n\n### 5. Set environment variables (persist in CI config)\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=\"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT\"\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/platform-tools:$PATH\"\n```\n\n### 6. Build\n\n```bash\ndotnet build -f net10.0-android -c Release\n```\n\n---\n\n**How to find correct versions if things change:**\n\n| Dependency | How to find the right version |\n|---|---|\n| Android API level | `grep android:targetSdkVersion` in your `.csproj` TargetFramework, or check `AutoImport.props` in the installed Android SDK pack |\n| Build-tools | Match the API level (e.g., API 35 → build-tools 35.x.x) |\n| JDK | [Microsoft docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/maui/get-started/installation) — currently JDK 17 |\n| Command-line tools | Always use `_latest.zip` from Google's download page |\n\nThe critical insight: **install the MAUI workload first**, then read its manifests to know exactly which Android SDK components to install — don't guess.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9f3cd0ca-21ee-44e2-9206-a1e4cdc684db","outputTokens":881,"requestId":"A421:30E8DC:5F2CF70:679D723:69F004B3"},"id":"6ef1c5cb-4728-4577-a7b8-e7dadb2a71bf","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:52:20.535Z","parentId":"20257ec6-9868-46b5-a746-cf040b4f4024"}
